.\" WSLMole man page
.TH WSLMOLE 1 "February 2026" "WSLMole 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wslmole \- WSL system optimization tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wslmole
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wslmole
is a terminal-based system optimization tool built for WSL2 (Windows Subsystem
for Linux) environments. It scans, cleans, and tunes your WSL instance through
an interactive whiptail TUI or direct CLI commands.
.PP
Running
.B wslmole
with no arguments launches the interactive TUI menu.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B clean
System cleanup: APT cache, snap revisions, log files, temp files, browser
cache, user data, and WSL-specific cleanup.
.TP
.B disk \fR[\fIpath\fR]
Disk usage analysis with multiple view modes including summary, tree view,
largest files/folders, file type breakdown, and old file detection.
.TP
.B dev \fR[\fIpath\fR]
Developer artifact cleanup: node_modules, target, __pycache__, .gradle, venv,
build, dist, and other build artifacts.
.TP
.B diagnose \fR[\fItype\fR]
System diagnostics: top processes, memory breakdown, systemd service status,
and WSL resource information.
.TP
.B packages \fR[\fIaction\fR]
Package manager wrapper for APT and Snap: audit updates, upgrade packages,
autoremove unused dependencies, clean caches, and list installed packages.
.TP
.B wsl \fR[\fIaction\fR]
WSL-specific tools: environment info, memory configuration, virtual disk
compact guide, and Windows interop status.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Launch the interactive TUI menu.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quick
Run a quick system health scan with score and recommendations.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging to ~/.local/share/wslmole/wslmole.log.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " FORMAT"
Output format:
.B text
(default) or
.BR json .
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Skip all confirmation prompts.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version number.
.SH CLEAN OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Preview what would be cleaned without deleting anything.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Skip all confirmation prompts.
.TP
.BI \-c ", " \-\-category " LIST"
Comma-separated list of categories to clean:
.BR apt ", " snap ", " logs ", " tmp ", " browser ", " user ", " wsl ", " all .
.SH DISK OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-m ", " \-\-mode " MODE"
Analysis mode:
.BR summary ", " tree ", " files ", " folders ", " types ", " old .
Default:
.BR summary .
.TP
.BI \-d ", " \-\-depth " N"
Tree depth for tree mode. Default: 3.
.TP
.BI \-n ", " \-\-top " N"
Number of results to show. Default: 10.
.SH DEV OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Preview artifacts without deleting.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Skip confirmation prompts.
.TP
.BI \-t ", " \-\-types " LIST"
Comma-separated artifact types:
.BR node_modules ", " target ", " __pycache__ ", " .gradle ", " venv ", "
.BR .venv ", " build ", " dist ", " .next ", " .nuxt ", " .cache ", "
.BR vendor ", " .tox ", " .pytest_cache ", " coverage ", " .nyc_output ", " all .
.TP
.BI \-\-older\-than " DAYS"
Only target artifacts older than DAYS days.
.SH DIAGNOSE TYPES
.TP
.B all
Run all diagnostics (default).
.TP
.B process
Top CPU and memory consuming processes.
.TP
.B memory
Memory usage breakdown with visual progress bar.
.TP
.B service
Systemd service status and resource usage.
.TP
.B wsl
WSL-specific environment and resource info.
.SH PACKAGES ACTIONS
.TP
.B audit
Check for available APT and Snap updates (default).
.TP
.B update
Update all APT and Snap packages.
.TP
.B autoremove
Remove unused APT dependencies.
.TP
.B clean
Clean APT cache and report old Snap revisions.
.TP
.B list
List installed APT and Snap packages.
.SH WSL ACTIONS
.TP
.B info
WSL environment info, .wslconfig, and /etc/wsl.conf (default).
.TP
.B memory
Memory allocation, usage, and .wslconfig limits.
.TP
.B compact
Guide to compacting the WSL2 virtual disk (vhdx).
.TP
.B interop
Windows/Linux interop status and PATH integration.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Launch interactive menu:
.B wslmole
.TP
Quick health scan:
.B wslmole \-q
.TP
Preview all cleanup categories:
.B wslmole clean \-\-dry\-run
.TP
Clean APT and log files only:
.B wslmole clean \-c apt,logs
.TP
Find 20 largest files in home directory:
.B wslmole disk ~ \-m files \-n 20
.TP
Clean old developer artifacts:
.B wslmole dev ~/projects \-\-older\-than 30
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/wslmole/wslmole.log
Log file (when \-\-verbose is enabled). Rotated at 1MB.
.TP
.I ~/.config/wslmole/config
Optional configuration file sourced at startup.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error or blocked operation.
.TP
.B 2
Resource not found.
.TP
.B 3
Permission denied.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/mrelph/WSLMole/issues
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wsl.exe (1)
